"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348434","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-08","<p>The Government’s commitment to save £12bn from welfare spending was set out in its election manifesto. Further details will be given in due course.</p>",,"Lord Freud","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348434/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T16:08:41.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348434/answer","Biography information for Lord Freud","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348434/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-03","Welfare State","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when they plan to publish details of the proposal in the Conservative party's manifesto to reduce the welfare budget by £12 billion by the 2017–18 financial year, and in particular their assessment of how it will affect pensions.","false","Biography information for Lord Hylton",,"Lord Hylton","HL246"
