"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347947","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-08","<p>The Department has made no estimates of future local government expenditure. Local government spending will be dependent upon future Spending Reviews as well as on other decisions, for example on local taxes and fees and charges.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347947/answer",,,,,"896","2015-06-08T13:29:37.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347947/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347947/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-02","Local Government Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate his Department has made of projected local government finance settlement spending for each of the next five years as (a) total expenditure and (b) a percentage of gross domestic product.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","895"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347948","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-08","<p>The Department has made no estimates of future local government expenditure. Local government spending will be dependent upon future Spending Reviews as well as on other decisions, for example on local taxes and fees and charges.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347948/answer",,,,,"895","2015-06-08T13:29:37.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347948/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347948/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-02","Local Government Finance: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate his Department has made of projected local government finance settlement spending in the West Midlands in each of the next five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","896"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347949","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-08","<p>There have been no such discussions between the Secretary of State and other Ministers with NATO and the EU, nor have there been such discussions at official level. The Royal Navy takes this issue particularly seriously and has a Fishery Liaison Officer to provide a central point of contact with the UK Fishing Industry, as well as regular consultation with fishermen's associations, training for personnel, and strict rules and procedures on reporting any incidents that might occur.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347949/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T15:47:59.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347949/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347949/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-02","Submarines: Irish Sea","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he has held with NATO and the EU on the effect of submarine activity on fishing in the Irish Sea in April 2015.","false","Biography information for Baroness Ritchie of Downpatrick","South Down","Ms Margaret Ritchie","813"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347950","Department of Health","false","2015-06-10","<p>The diabetes prevention programme announced seven demonstrator sites on 12 March 2015:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>- Birmingham South and Central Clinical Commissioning Group (CCG)</p><p> </p><p>- Bradford City CCG</p><p> </p><p>- Durham County Council</p><p> </p><p>- Herefordshire CCG/Local Authority (LA)</p><p> </p><p>- Medway CCG/LA</p><p> </p><p>- Salford CCG/LA</p><p> </p><p>- Southwark Council and CCG</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The demonstrator sites were specifically chosen with different levels of service provision to provide important learning in establishing the National Diabetes Prevention Programme. Six demonstrator sites have existing type 2 diabetes prevention services.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The programme is currently working with the demonstrator sites to jointly develop plans to amend and scale up their services. This will inform the development of the programme.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347950/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-10T14:22:16.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347950/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347950/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-02","Diabetes: Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, in which of the seven demonstrator sites the NHS National Diabetes Prevention Programme began operating.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","828"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347951","Department of Health","false","2015-06-10","<p>This information is not held centrally.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Public Health England (PHE) is currently working with the health &amp; social care information centre to establish a national data standard which will allow uniformed reporting on the NHS Health Check. PHE is also exploring options for the introduction of a national for representational data collection system for the NHS health check programme.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347951/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-10T14:59:25.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347951/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347951/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-02","Diabetes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many patients have been identified as possibly diabetic by the NHS Health Check in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","829"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347952","Department of Health","false","2015-06-09","<p>School nurses have a role in the primary prevention of obesity in children and young people. The National Diabetes Prevention Programme is aimed at individuals at high risk of developing type 2 diabetes aged over 18, and as such school nurses will not have a role in this programme.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347952/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-09T12:26:37.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347952/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347952/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-02","Diabetes: Nurses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether school nurses will have a role in the National Diabetes Prevention Programme.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","830"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347953","Department of Health","false","2015-06-09","<p>For the 12 months between 1 January 2014 to 31 December 2014, 1,471,926 people received an NHS Health Check. This is the latest complete data set covering 12 months.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347953/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-09T12:30:01.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347953/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347953/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-02","Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many patients have been assessed by the NHS Health Check in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","831"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347954","Department for International Development","false","2015-06-09","<p>DFID programmes in Yemen support the UK’s vision for a more stable, secure and prosperous Yemen by helping to manage crises and tackle the drivers of conflict and poverty. Given the current context, DFID’s principal focus is on meeting the immediate humanitarian needs of millions of Yemeni people.</p><p> </p><p>So far the UK has provided £15 million to the 2015 UN Humanitarian Appeal for Yemen (including an additional commitment of £4 million in April 2015). Our contribution is providing life-saving assistance (e.g. medical supplies, water, food and emergency shelter) to those affected by the conflict and treating severe acute malnutrition. We have temporarily suspended or closed other programmes which supported political and economic reform.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>More detailed information about all DFID-funded programmes can be found at: <a href="http://devtracker.dfid.gov.uk/countries/YE/" target="_blank">http://devtracker.dfid.gov.uk/countries/YE/</a>.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347954/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-09T16:42:24.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347954/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347954/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-06-02","Yemen: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what programmes her Department is operating (a) in Yemen and (b) to address the implications of the conflict in that country.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","832"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347955","Department for International Development","false","2015-06-09","<p>The United Nations Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs (OCHA) reports that since 26 March, the start of the most recent hostilities, over 1 million Yemenis have been internally displaced (in addition to an estimated 335,000 internally displaced people prior to March). OCHA anticipates that this number is likely to increase as the conflict continues and data improves. For the same period, the International Organisation for Migration (IOM) reports that over 25,000 people (Yemenis and foreign nationals) have fled to neighbouring countries, mainly to Djibouti and Somalia.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347955/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-09T16:41:32.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347955/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347955/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-06-02","Yemen: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what estimate she has made of the number of refugees (a) within and (b) outside Yemen as a result of the ongoing conflict in that country.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","833"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347956","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-09","<p>The Government attaches great importance to the support of human rights around the world, in Mexico, as elsewhere. We share longstanding and serious concerns with the international community about reports of human rights violations and impunity in Mexico. We encourage efforts by the Mexican government to strengthen processes and mechanisms to prevent human rights violations and ensure that those responsible for violations are brought to justice. Indeed, the Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron), discussed human rights with President Peña Nieto during his State Visit to the UK in March this year. Through a programme of visits, meetings and discussions with representatives of the Mexican government, human rights defenders, non-governmental organisations and international partners, we hope these efforts will build respect for fundamental human rights and strengthen rule of law in Mexico. We continue to support human rights organisations on the ground and share UK experience of tackling the challenges Mexico faces. We are currently focusing on the treatment of torture and enforced disappearance by judges, and are in the process of selecting projects to address security and justice concerns which will complement this work.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347956/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-09T14:29:36.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347956/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347956/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-02","Mexico: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment his Department has made of human rights in Mexico.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","834"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347957","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-09","<p>The UK is committed to regular dialogue on a range of issues of mutual interest with the Mexican government as part of our positive bilateral relationship.</p><p>While we assess that Mexico does not pose a direct threat to the UK as a source country or transit route for narcotics, our Embassy works closely with the Mexican government to strengthen its ability to tackle its security challenges and the rule of law.</p><p>The Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend, the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond), discussed counter–narcotics with his Mexican counterpart in February.</p><p>The Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend, the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron), discussed Mexico's broader security challenges with President Pena Nieto during the latter's State visit to the UK in March.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347957/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-09T14:08:53.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347957/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347957/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-02","Mexico: Smuggling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions his Department has had with the government of Mexico on drug trafficking.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","840"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347958","Wales Office","false","2015-06-08","<p>My office is in regular contact with Department for Transport and Highways England officials. I have made clear that I expect to see this issue resolved as soon as possible. Highways England has provided assurances that it is aiming to complete the project within the next four weeks.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Preseli Pembrokeshire","Stephen Crabb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347958/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T14:36:17.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347958/answer","Biography information for Stephen Crabb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347958/answer",,,,,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2015-06-02","Roads: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, when (a) he and (b) his Department have made (i) oral and (ii) written representations to the Secretary of State for Transport on the time taken of work carried out at the A55/A493 junction.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","752"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347959","Leader of the House","false","2015-06-08","<p>The Government will bring forward its proposals for ‘English Votes for English Laws’ in this Parliamentary Session. They will reflect a great deal of careful consideration, building on the work undertaken by the former Leader of the House in the last Parliament. The proposals will complement the further devolution of powers and ensure fairness to all parts of the UK. It will be for Members of Parliament to have the final say on them.</p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347959/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T16:39:08.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347959/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347959/answer",,,,,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2015-06-02","Members: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, what consultation he has carried out in Wales on the Government's proposal to change the role of hon. Members representing constituencies in Wales in the scrutiny of legislation.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","753"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347960","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-08","<p>The Road Haulage Association estimates a current shortage of HGV drivers at around 45,000 and I am aware the shortage has put operational and financial pressures onto the industry. I have met industry representatives and discussed the issue.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Work continues on improving the accessibility of HGV driving tests in those areas where there are significant waits, in the context of recent increases in demand and a pass rate of about 54%. Discussions are continuing with industry and involving other government departments to improve recruitment and reduce administrative delays, including in respect of the costs of training, training effectiveness to achieve test passes and the attractiveness of the profession.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347960/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T15:53:10.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347960/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347960/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-02","Large Goods Vehicle Drivers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the adequacy of the number of qualified heavy goods vehicle drivers; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","751"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347961","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-08","<p>I refer my Honourable friend to the answers I gave 1 June 2015, UINs 4 and 13.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347961/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T14:42:45.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347961/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/347961/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-02","Revenue and Customs: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent assessment he has made of the time taken by HM Revenue and Customs to answer telephone calls from members of the public; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","890"
