"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348015","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-09","We are aware of the deeply troubling reports of bombings in Kauda, Sudan on 25 May. The recent escalation of fighting in the Two Areas of Southern Kordofan and Blue Nile is extremely concerning and we will continue to press both the Government of Sudan and the SPLM-North (Sudan People's Liberation Movement - North) for an end to military action.","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348015/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-09T13:20:51.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348015/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348015/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-02","South Sudan: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what reports he has received on the bombing of a church, school compound and priests' compound in Kauda, South Sudan, on 25 May 2015.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","758"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348016","Department of Health","false","2015-06-10","<p>Data on waiting times to see a general practitioner is not collected.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348016/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-10T16:00:53.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348016/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348016/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-02","General Practitioners: Sheffield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people were waiting to see a GP for more than one week in (a) Sheffield, Heeley constituency and (b) Sheffield in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","703"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348017","Department for Education","false","2015-06-09","<p>The department supports the removal of asbestos from schools, where it is safe and appropriate to do so, through its capital funding schemes.</p><p> </p><p>We are spending £1.4 billion to improve the condition of the school estate in financial year 2015 to 2016. The majority of this £1.4 billion (over £950 million) goes directly to schools and those responsible for them, and it is for them to decide how to use this funding to address their needs, including to manage and remove asbestos where appropriate. The legal responsibility for managing asbestos in schools rests with local authorities, academy trusts, governing bodies and other duty holders and so we rightly provide them with the flexibility to use their funding to carry out this duty.</p><p> </p><p>The remainder of the £1.4 billion goes through the Condition Improvement Fund (CIF), which provides more than £430 million to address the condition needs of academies in small multi-academy trusts and single academy trusts, as well as sixth-form colleges. This includes funding projects that remove asbestos from schools, as well as projects that will encapsulate asbestos, rather than removing it.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, where schools are being refurbished or rebuilt by the department as part of the Priority School Building Programmes, through which we will invest around £4bn, the costs of any asbestos management work, including removing it – where that is appropriate – are being met by the department. We do not make a specific allowance for asbestos works in a scheme. This is managed alongside other site risks. We allow 17% of the capital cost of a scheme for these risks and a central contingency is held for exceptional cases. This spending is often incorporated into the wider costs associated with demolition or refurbishment work.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348017/answer",,,,,"845","2015-06-09T16:15:07.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348017/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348017/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-06-02","Schools: Asbestos","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what additional funding she has provided to schools for the removal of asbestos in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","710"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348018","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-09","<p /> <p>The Student Loans Company is carrying out an analysis to identify loan payments made in relation to adults in the Sheffield, Heeley constituency. The information will be placed in the Libraries of the House as soon as possible.</p><p> </p><p>In relation to part (b) the most recent Student Loans Company report (published on 25<sup>th</sup> March 2015) on payments made to FE providers on behalf of loans-funded learners shows that during the 2013/14 academic year a total of £115.8m was paid out, and in the first six months of the 2014/15 academic year £65m has been paid.</p><p> </p><p>The full report is available through the following link:</p><p><a href="http://www.slc.co.uk/official-statistics/financial-support-awarded/england-further-education.aspx" target="_blank">http://www.slc.co.uk/official-statistics/financial-support-awarded/england-further-education.aspx</a></p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348018/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-09T09:37:24.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348018/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348018/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-02","Mature Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how much was borrowed by adults in (a) Sheffield, Heeley constituency and (b) England in 24+ advanced learning loans in the last year.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","771"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348019","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-09","<p>The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS) models the proportion of loans which we expect will not be repaid - the resource accounting and budgeting charge (RAB charge). The RAB charge is estimated to be 50% of the total loan amount. BIS is collecting data on learners as it emerges and based on this data we regularly review and update the RAB charge estimates.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We publish the RAB charge once a year in the Department’s accounts.</p><p> </p><p />","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348019/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-09T09:28:50.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348019/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348019/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-02","Mature Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what estimate he has made of the proportion of money borrowed under 24+ advanced learning loans that will be repaid to the Exchequer.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","772"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348020","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-09","<p /> <p>The Government has commissioned a programme of loans evaluation which will be published in due course, once completed.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348020/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-09T10:11:59.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348020/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348020/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-02","Mature Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the effect of 24+ advanced learning loans on participation levels in further education.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","773"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348021","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-12","<p>Apprenticeships benefit individuals, employers and the economy. That is why we have made a commitment to deliver 3 million apprenticeship starts during this Parliament.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As part of the 3 million starts, there will be many more advanced and higher level apprenticeships, which in turn will widen access to the professions and develop the higher technical skills needed to improve productivity and support industry. There will also be more Degree apprenticeships which allow young people to combine a world-class degree with a world class-apprenticeship route.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We will say more about the detail of our plans to deliver 3 million apprenticeships in due course.</p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348021/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-12T13:37:13.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348021/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348021/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-02","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps he plans to take to increase the number of advanced level apprenticeships.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","774"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348022","Department for Education","false","2015-06-10","<p>The information requested is not available.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Education publishes statistics on teacher retention that show the percentage of all teachers that remain in service after their initial qualification, by length of service. These statistics are not produced by subject of qualification held by teachers or by the subject taught by teachers. The latest information is published online in Table C2 of the additional tables at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/school-workforce-in-england-november-2013" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/statistics/school-workforce-in-england-november-2013</a></p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348022/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-10T15:30:49.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348022/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348022/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-06-02","Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many STEM teachers remain in the teaching profession (a) two years and (b) five years after their initial qualification.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","851"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348023","Department for Education","false","2015-06-10","<p>Teach First do not retain records for those starting the programme but do retain the data of their programme participants who go on to become ambassadors for the programme. After 2 years, 63% of Teach First ambassadors were still in teaching and after 5 years 56% of ambassadors were still in teaching.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348023/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-10T15:35:01.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348023/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348023/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-06-02","Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many Teach First teachers remain in the teaching profession after (a) two years and (b) five years.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","852"
