"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348096","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-10","<p>No shipborne rolling vertical landings have taken place with an F-35B. The plan is to commence this activity in 2018 as part of First of Class Flying Trials. Ahead of these trials there is a range of de-risking work being undertaken which includes aircraft trials and synthetic modelling. The concept has already been demonstrated on the French carrier Charles de Gaulle using a modified Harrier aircraft. The primary approach aid was tested on HMS Illustrious.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348096/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-10T16:32:06.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348096/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348096/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-02","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many successful shipborne rolling vertical landings have taken place using the F-35B with (a) an empty weapons load and (b) the maximum weight weapons configuration to date.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","790"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348097","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-10","<p>The F-35B has not yet entered frontline service with the UK Armed Forces. A single RAF test pilot is at Naval Air Station Patuxant River as part of the multi-national integrated test force. A joint team of RAF and Royal Navy pilots is at Edwards Air Force Base operating as part of the multi-national team undertaking operational test and evaluation. While clearance for operational use of night vision (enhancement) continues in the multi-national test team, UK pilots have completed no night landings using the system. However, UK pilots have completed 20 conventional visual night landings.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348097/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-10T16:30:57.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348097/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348097/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-02","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many successful night landings of the Joint Strike Fighter F-35B have been conducted by RAF pilots using night vision.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","791"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348098","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-10","<p>The F-35 night vision and distributed aperture system capabilities are still under developmental test and have not been cleared for operational use by the US or any other F-35 partner nation when landing on a carrier at night.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348098/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-10T16:29:50.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348098/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348098/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-02","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether Joint Strike Fighter F-35s are allowed to use (a) night vision and (b) the distributed aperture system when landing on an aircraft carrier at night.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","792"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348099","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-09","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 27 January 2015, to Question 221410, to the hon. Member for Moray (Mr Robertson).</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348099/answer","20150127_Hansard extract on European Fighter Aircraft.doc","20150127_Hansard extract on European Fighter Aircraft.doc","20150127 - QnA extract on European Fighter Airaft","20150127 - QnA extract on European Fighter Airaft",,"2015-06-09T15:19:06.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348099/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348099/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-02","European Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will publish details of the programme to install a Collision Warning System in the Typhoon aircraft.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","793"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348100","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-10","<p>A copy of the document <em>D/VCDS&amp;2ndPUS/8/1/4 PR11 Tornado CWS Further Work</em> is attached.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348100/answer","20110707SafetyFurtherWorkTORS_2ndPUS_3_3_16[1][1].doc","20110707SafetyFurtherWorkTORS_2ndPUS_3_3_16[1][1].doc","794 - PR11 Tornado CWS Further Work","794 - PR11 Tornado CWS Further Work",,"2015-06-10T16:31:25.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348100/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348100/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-02","Tornado Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will place in the Library a copy of the document D/VCDS&2ndPUS/8/1/4 PR11 Tornado CWS Further Work, identified in paragraph 1.4.6.606 of the Report into the Tornado collision of 3 July 2012 undertaken by the Director-General of the Military Aviation Authority.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","794"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348101","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-08","<p>The current contract is for a single prototype system and valued at £13 Million. If successful, this system will be converted for operational use and further systems may be procured with associated Hunt Class modifications.</p><p>The dates for Initial and Full Operating Capability have not yet been determined and are subject to a Main Gate investment decision, which is expected in 2019. The permanent base for this equipment will be Her Majesty's Naval Base Portsmouth, which is where the Hunt Class Mine Countermeasures Vessels are currently based.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348101/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T15:06:29.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348101/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348101/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-02","Minesweepers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when the Autonomous Minesweeping Capability will achieve (a) initial and (b) full operational capability; what the total cost of the programme is; and where the assets developed will be permanently based.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","811"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348102","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-08","<p>The contract for the autonomous minesweeping capability was placed with Atlas Elektronik UK on 26 February 2015. The value of the contract is £13 million. BAE Systems and Babcock Marine are subcontractors to Atlas Elektronik UK. The proportion of the value of this contract that will go to Atlas, BAE Systems and Babcock Marine is approximately 70%, 26% and 4% respectively.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348102/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T15:45:43.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348102/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348102/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-02","Minesweepers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will estimate the proportion of the value of the UK Ministry of Defence Autonomous Minesweeping Capability contract that will go to (a) Atlas Elektronik (b) BAE systems and (c) Babcock.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","812"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348103","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-08","<p>The Government will respond to the House of Lords Economic Affairs Committee's report “The Economics of High Speed 2” shortly. We are confident the case for HS2 is robust and look forward to clarifying the issues the Committee has raised.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348103/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T12:35:09.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348103/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348103/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-02","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he plans to publish the Government's response to the House of Lords Economic Affairs Committee's First Report of Session 2014-15, The Economics of High Speed 2, HL Paper 134.","false","Biography information for Keir Starmer","Holborn and St Pancras","Keir Starmer","934"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348104","Department for International Development","false","2015-06-08","<p>The UK is a key supporter of the Africa-led movement to end Female Genital Mutilation. We have made the largest single donor commitment ever to this issue, with a flagship programme of £35 million over 5 years.</p><p> </p><p>In addition DFID is exploring what we can do in practising countries where we have bilateral programmes, including supporting efforts to end FGM in Sudan (which has a very high prevalence rate) through a £12m bilateral five year programme.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We also continue to work with others to increase international commitment to this neglected issue. DFID’s Girl Summit, held in July 2014, resulted in commitments to take action to end FGM and child, early and forced marriage (CEFM) from organisations, governments, businesses, communities and individuals across the world.</p>","Putney","Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348104/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T12:48:22.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348104/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348104/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-06-02","Female Genital Mutilation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department is taking to support anti-FGM measures.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","935"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348105","Department for International Development","false","2015-06-08","<p>The UK is committed to supporting efforts to end female genital mutilation both in the UK and across the globe. We welcome the passing of the Violence Against Persons Prohibition Bill and its ban on female genital mutilation in Nigeria. DFID will work closely with the new Government on the implementation of this Bill. DFID is also supporting implementation at both federal and state levels.</p>","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348105/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T16:11:08.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348105/answer","Biography information for Grant Shapps","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348105/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-06-02","Nigeria: Female Genital Mutilation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps she plans to take to support the implementation of the ban on female genital mutilation in Nigeria.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","936"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348106","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-10","<p>Consumers can retain their telephone numbers when switching provider through an established process called number porting. Ofcom imposes obligations, through its General Conditions, on all landline and mobile providers to safeguard the interests of consumers wishing to port their numbers.</p><p> </p><p>When switching mobile provider, the consumer requests a porting authorisation code (PAC) from the existing provider and gives it to the new provider, allowing the mobile number to be transferred to the new network. Although the losing provider may charge the consumer, there are safeguards: a provider cannot refuse to issue a PAC unless specific circumstances apply (for example, if the consumer cannot adequately prove that he/she is the legitimate account holder). Ofcom requires PACs to be issued immediately over the phone or within two hours by text message. Consumers are entitled to compensation if a number is not ported within one working day from the new provider receiving the PAC. Ofcom can take action against companies that repeatedly breach these rules and has the power to fine providers up to 10% of annual turnover</p><p> </p><p>For consumers switching landline providers, the losing provider must allow an active telephone number to be transferred to a new provider, assuming the consumer is staying at the same address. Although gaining providers are not required by Ofcom to accept a request to transfer, it is plainly in their interests to do so and, in most cases, they do accept such requests; if it does accept the request, the gaining provider should make all transfer arrangements. Where consumers move address but remain within the same telephone exchange, providers may allow consumers to retain their telephone numbers but that process is not regulated by Ofcom. If he/she moves outside the local exchange, a consumer will not usually be able to keep the same number on a traditional landline; it is possible, however, to do so by porting the number to a VoIP service for a one-off fee.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348106/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-10T09:25:52.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348106/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348106/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-02","Telephone Numbering","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he is taking to safeguard consumers who wish to keep their current telephone number when switching providers; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","927"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348107","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-09","<p>Following the introduction of Individual Electoral Registration (IER) in Great Britain in 2014, the annual canvass of households has been retained. There are no current plans to exercise an order under Part 1, Section 7(2)(b) of the Electoral Registration and Administration Act 2013.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348107/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-09T15:27:23.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348107/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348107/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-06-02","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what his policy is on the abolition of the annual canvass undertaken by Electoral Registration Officers, as provided for in the Electoral Registration and Administration Act 2013 c. 6 Part 1, Section 7(2)(b), during the course of the current Parliament.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","696"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348108","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-06-09","<p>The Government was elected with a mandate to reform and modernise the UK human rights framework. The UK has a proud tradition of respect for human rights which long pre-dates the 1998 Human Rights Act. The 1998 Act opened the system to abuse, which has damaged the credibility of human rights. <br><br>We will bring forward proposals for a British Bill of Rights, which will replace the Human Rights Act. Our Bill will protect fundamental human rights, but also prevent their abuse and restore common sense to the system. <br><br>We will fully consult on our proposals before introducing legislation.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348108/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-09T14:18:51.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348108/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348108/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-06-02","Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will consult on a British Bill of Rights before its introduction; if he will publish the terms of reference for such a consultation; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","697"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348109","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-09","<p>The Government remains committed to equalising the size of constituencies in order to make votes of more equal value. The Government will outline its plans for constituency boundaries when it responds to the Political and Constitutional Reform Committee’s report, <em>What next on the redrawing of parliamentary constituency boundaries?</em>, in due course.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348109/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-09T11:57:42.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348109/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348109/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-06-02","Constituencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether the Government plans to bring forward legislative proposals to alter the procedure by which the recommendations of the Boundary Commissions take effect upon the conclusion of their periodic reviews of constituency boundaries.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","698"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348110","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-08","<p>Details regarding the Edith Cavell commemorative coin are available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.royalmint.com/aboutus/news/royal-mint-honours-edith-cavell" target="_blank">http://www.royalmint.com/aboutus/news/royal-mint-honours-edith-cavell</a>.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348110/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T16:19:53.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348110/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348110/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-02","Edith Cavell: Commemorative Coins","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will take steps to ensure that the Edith Cavell commemorative coin recently issued by the Royal Mint can be purchased by members of the public at an affordable price.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","711"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348111","Department for Education","false","2015-06-08","<p>The Department for Education does not offer separate specific guidance to local authorities regarding the choices available for parents at grammar and local authority maintained schools.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The School Admissions Code provides that local authorities must offer information to parents regarding the choices of state-funded schools available in their local area, through their composite prospectus.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348111/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T15:58:43.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348111/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348111/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-06-02","School Choice","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will revise the guidance offered to LEAs regarding the choices available to parents who seek a place for their child at both grammar and LEA schools.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","750"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348112","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-05","<p>I will write to the hon. Member when the information is available and place a copy in the Library of the House.</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348112/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-05T12:28:17.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348112/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348112/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-02","Armed Forces: Mefloquine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 1 June 2015 to Question 126, when he expects to be able to place in the Library the correspondence between his Department and Public Health England in relation to use of Lariam or Mefloquine and reports of (a) hallucinations, (b) psychosis and (c) suicidal thoughts in personnel prescribed those medications for the period 2010 to 2015; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","739"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348113","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-10","<p>Since the publication of the UN Commission of Inquiry report on the human rights situation in the Democratic People’s Republic of Korea (DPRK), the UK has worked with the EU and our like-minded partners to ensure momentum is maintained on the human rights situation in the DPRK. This includes contributing to strong resolutions at the UN Human Rights Council and the UN General Assembly as well as supporting discussion of DPRK human rights by the UN Security Council in December 2014. We continue to discuss with other governments how the international community can work together to improve human rights in the DPRK.</p><p> </p><p>Existing UN and EU sanctions against the DPRK are based upon UN Security Council Resolutions prohibiting the further development of the DPRK’s nuclear and ballistic missile programmes. Any introduction of sanctions on human rights grounds would require the establishment of a new sanctions regime at UN or EU level. Identifying individuals or entities with the degree of legal certainty required for sanctions listing would be difficult. Existing sanctions against Iran and Russia (as a result of action in Ukraine) are both at the EU level. The UK does not impose unilateral sanctions.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348113/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-10T13:52:19.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348113/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348113/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-02","North Korea: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether the UK is able to identify those responsible for human rights violations in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea; and what steps the Government is taking to impose sanctions on North Korean officials similar to the financial sanctions imposed by HM Treasury on people responsible for serious human rights violations in Iran and Ukraine.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","726"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348114","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-18","<p>Earlier this month, the Chancellor wrote to the Governor of the Bank of England seeking his advice on when and how the return of the Government’s stake in RBS to the private sector should be undertaken; in view of the wide range of implications for financial stability, growth, and achieving the best returns for the taxpayer.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In his reply, the Governor stated that “it is in the public interest for the Government to begin now to return RBS to private ownership”, and warned that there could be considerable net costs to taxpayers of further delays to the start of a sale. This is also the conclusion of an independent review the Chancellor has commissioned on the issue, undertaken by Rothschild investment bank. The advice and the independent report have both been published online at www.gov.uk.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348114/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-18T11:07:15.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348114/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348114/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-02","Royal Bank of Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will commission an independent review of the Government's stake in the Royal Bank of Scotland.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart McDonald","754"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348115","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-18","<p>The Chancellor has previously set out his objectives for the banks in state ownership, including Royal Bank of Scotland. We want to get the best value for money for the taxpayer; and we want to return them to private ownership. This policy is supported by recent advice from the Governor of the Bank of England that “it is in the public interest for the Government to begin now to return RBS to the private sector”, and that “there could be considerable net costs to taxpayers of further delaying the start of a sale”.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348115/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-18T11:08:33.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348115/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348115/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-02","Royal Bank of Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will ensure that any review of the Government's stake in the Royal Bank of Scotland (a) includes representation and consultation with all stakeholders and (b) assesses the costs and benefits of all available options, including alternatives to reprivatisation.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart McDonald","755"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348116","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-10","<p>The Government’s shareholding in RBS is managed at arm’s length from HM Treasury by UK Financial Investments. Any decisions relating to the bank’s commercial operations remain a matter for the bank’s independent management team.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348116/answer",,,,,"757","2015-06-10T15:22:08.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348116/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348116/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-02","Royal Bank of Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions he has had with the Royal Bank of Scotland on plans to close further branches; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart McDonald","756"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348117","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-10","<p>The Government’s shareholding in RBS is managed at arm’s length from HM Treasury by UK Financial Investments. Any decisions relating to the bank’s commercial operations remain a matter for the bank’s independent management team.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348117/answer",,,,,"756","2015-06-10T15:22:08.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348117/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348117/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-02","Royal Bank of Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if the Government will take steps to prevent further closure of branches of the Royal Bank of Scotland pending a review of such closure.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart McDonald","757"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348118","Home Office","false","2015-06-05","<p>I have not received any representations from Welsh Ministers or Assembly Members about the Dyfed Powys helicopter or the National Police Air Service (NPAS). NPAS is an operational policing co-ordination initiative independent of the Home Office; but we support the Strategic Board in their work to provide an effective and efficient air service in England and Wales.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348118/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-05T15:16:03.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348118/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348118/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-06-02","Police: Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what representations she has received from Welsh Assembly Ministers about the (a) Dyfed Powys Police Helicopter and (b) National Police Air Service.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","760"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348119","Wales Office","false","2015-06-09","<p>Wales Office Ministers have not received any representations from Welsh Ministers or Assembly Members about the Dyfed Powys helicopter or the National Police Air Service (NPAS).</p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348119/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-09T16:20:17.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348119/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348119/answer",,,,,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2015-06-02","Police: Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what representations he has received from Ministers in the Welsh Government about the (a) Dyfed Powys Police Helicopter and (b) National Police Air Service.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","761"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348120","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-09","<p>The EU has worked closely with like-minded partners to ensure momentum is maintained on the human rights situation in the Democratic People’s Republic of Korea (DPRK). This has included sponsoring strong resolutions in both the UN Human Rights Council and the UN General Assembly. While the EU does not maintain a development aid budget with the DPRK, the EU does provide funding for a food nutrition programme targeted at the most vulnerable DPRK citizens with a current average annual value of €6 million. <br> <br>Like the UK, EU member states also fund a range of bilateral programmes within the DPRK. While a direct impact on human rights is not a condition for EU projects, the impact of projects on the DPRK human rights situation is carefully considered. The UK intends to continue working closely with other EU member states to ensure areas of concern continue to be addressed. The EU is willing to consider engagement with the DPRK government through dialogue when it includes discussion of the human rights situation.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348120/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-09T14:27:24.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348120/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348120/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-02","North Korea: EU Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what human rights conditions are required of the government of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea for European-funded aid projects in that country; if he will press for greater use of such conditions; and what assessment he has made of the effect of such projects.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","782"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348121","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-10","<p>The UK’s policy of critical engagement enables us to directly express to the Democratic People’s Republic of Korea (DPRK), the UK and international community’s concerns regarding the DPRK’s nuclear weapons programme and human rights situation. We use educational and cultural projects to encourage the DPRK citizens/population to better understand the outside world and the opportunities that reform, including on human rights, could bring. The UN Commission of Inquiry report on the human rights situation in the DPRK recommended that States and civil society organisations foster opportunities for people-to-people dialogue and contact in areas including culture. While a direct impact on human rights is not a condition for all Foreign and Commonwealth Office engagement projects, we consider carefully the impact of all project activities on the human rights situation in the DPRK when deciding whether or not to undertake a project.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348121/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-10T13:57:05.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348121/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348121/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-02","North Korea: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what human rights conditions are attached to the UK's cultural engagement projects inside the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","783"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348122","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-09","<p>In line with Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) Strategic and Bilateral Programme Fund guidance, all projects, wherever they are implemented, are subject to regular monitoring and review during implementation and on completion, with high value projects subject to further evaluation. This ensures each project supports wider FCO Programme objectives and foreign policy priorities and delivers outputs in an efficient, effective and sustainable manner. This includes projects implemented in the Democratic People’s Republic of Korea (DPRK), where (in line with FCO project management practices) reporting considers the impact of project outputs, which are managed and delivered by our Embassy in Pyongyang and its implementing partners in the DPRK, and which may also incorporate discussions with DPRK citizens who have participated in, and benefitted from, FCO funded projects.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348122/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-09T14:13:29.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348122/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348122/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-02","North Korea","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what monitoring mechanisms there were of the effect on the people of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea of engagement projects funded by his Department in that country between 2010 and 2015.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","784"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348123","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-08","<p>My Department does not monitor the purchases of property by foreign buyers.</p><p> </p><p>The housing market is at the heart of our long-term economic plan – getting homes built, creating new homeowners and delivering hundreds of thousands of jobs. Foreign investment is helping to deliver new housing for UK residents and supporting jobs and long-term economic growth.</p><p> </p><p>Following the financial crisis and subsequent recession, foreign investment in new housing has been helping to provide the finance needed to build homes. Without upfront investment from buyers, financiers would not have released the cash needed for development to go ahead, and building would have stalled.</p><p> </p><p>These new developments not only provide homes, they also unlock associated affordable housing development In 2013, Savills suggested in their report “Spotlight World in London” that international sales of newly built properties helped to finance 3,000 new affordable homes that may otherwise not have been built.</p><p> </p><p>In their report of July 2014, Savills estimate that “those buying an investment property from overseas only account for an estimated 7 per cent of all greater London residential transactions”.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348123/answer",,,,,"933","2015-06-08T13:25:07.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348123/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348123/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-02","Housing: Foreign Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether his Department has a mechanism in place to monitor whether foreign buyers of UK property are occupants, landlords, UK business owners or absentee property investors.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","799"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348124","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-08","<p /> <p>The Information requested is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348124/answer",,,,,"894","2015-06-08T10:15:00.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348124/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348124/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-02","Social Security Benefits: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many combined employment and support allowance and personal independence payment claimants with mental ill health have had their application undergo a mandatory reconsideration since October 2013.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","800"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348125","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-08","The information requested can be obtained from the Child Benefit Statistics Geographical Analysis August 2014 publication which is available on gov.uk.<p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348125/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T16:25:59.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348125/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348125/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-02","Child Benefit: Warrington North","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people in Warrington North constituency are in receipt of child benefit for three or more children.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","805"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348126","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-08","<p /> <p>The Household Below Average Income (HBAI) publication, which provides the national estimates of child poverty as defined by the Child Poverty Act 2010, cannot be broken down below the level of region, due to sample size and coverage issues.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348126/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T10:22:07.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348126/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348126/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-02","Children: Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent estimate he has made of the number of children living in poverty in each ward of Warrington North constituency.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","806"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348127","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-09","<p>All Pacer vehicles on the Northern franchise will be withdrawn by 2020 due to incompatibility of the Pacer vehicles with the vision for economic growth and prosperity in the north as per announcement by the Secretary of State in February 2015.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348127/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-09T10:46:27.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348127/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348127/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-02","Rolling Stock: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what his Department's policy is on replacing pacer trains on rail services in the north of England.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","838"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348128","Home Office","false","2015-06-04","<p>There is already a medal available for long service and good conduct in the police, the Police Long Service and Good Conduct Medal (PLSGCM). King George VI instituted the PLSGCM in June 1951 by Royal Warrant for those who have rendered long and meritorious service as members of the Police Forces of the United Kingdom (UK), the Isle of Man and the Channel Islands. The PLSGCM is subject to the terms laid down in its Royal Warrant. The medal recognises police officers who have served twenty years and have demonstrated good conduct. There are no plans to change the PLSGCM or to introduce a new long service medal.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348128/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-04T14:50:03.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348128/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348128/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-06-02","Police: Long Service Awards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will introduce a Long Service Medal to recognise the contribution of long-serving police officers; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Keir Starmer","Holborn and St Pancras","Keir Starmer","839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348129","Department for Education","false","2015-06-10","<p>The Department for Education is currently considering what further support and encouragement can be provided to awarding organisations to enable as wide a range of languages as possible to be maintained at GCSE and A level.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The government has been clear that it wants to see all pupils provided with the opportunity to take a core set of academic subjects, including modern foreign languages. The number of pupils entering for a modern language GCSE has increased by 20% since 2010 due to the introduction of the English Baccalaureate. There are considerable benefits to learning a second language and the government is keen to see the range of languages at GCSE and A level preserved. To this end, the Secretary of State wrote to exam boards during the pre-election period in April to express her concern about their decision to stop awarding qualifications in some languages. She asked awarding organisations to work with Ofqual on the future of these qualifications and committed, if there is no further action, to launching a consultation on how best to secure the future of these qualifications.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348129/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-10T11:21:22.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348129/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348129/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-06-02","Languages: Qualifications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what her policy is on the future of A-levels and GCSEs for (a) Turkish, (b) Greek, (c) Gujarati, (d) Modern Hebrew, (e) Panjabi, (f) Polish, (g) Bengali and (h) other community languages; and if she will outline steps that will be taken in pursuit of that policy.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","842"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348130","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-09","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office’s (FCO) report on the human rights situation within the Democratic People’s Republic of Korea (DPRK), published 12 March, noted that “consistent reports suggest that sexual abuse and domestic violence is common [within the DPRK]”. During the DPRK’s 2014 Universal Periodic Review (UPR) of human rights at the UN in Geneva, the DPRK accepted 185 recommendations including several relating to women’s rights. Our officials recently met DPRK diplomats to discuss the progress the DPRK had made on implementing the accepted UPR recommendations and to request further information on steps the DPRK government was taking to address the recommendations.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348130/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-09T14:33:11.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348130/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348130/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-02","North Korea: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to his Department's report, Democratic People's Republic of Korea - Country of Concern, published on 12 March 2015, what steps the British Embassy in Pyongyang has taken to challenge widespread sexual abuse and domestic violence against women in that country.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","844"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348131","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-04","<p>The Government and EDF are continuing to work together to finalise the contract for the Hinkley project. EDF expects that Hinkley Point C will come online around 2023.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348131/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-04T15:38:27.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348131/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348131/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-02","Hinkley Point C Power Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what progress has been made in relation to the construction of Hinckley C nuclear power station; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Reynolds","Stalybridge and Hyde","Jonathan Reynolds","903"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348132","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-04","<p>Energy suppliers are required under licence conditions to take all reasonable steps to roll-out smart meters to all their domestic and smaller non-domestic customers by 31 December 2020.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348132/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-04T14:46:33.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348132/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348132/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-02","Energy: Meters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, when she expects the Smartmeter rollout to be completed.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Reynolds","Stalybridge and Hyde","Jonathan Reynolds","904"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348133","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-09","<p>With reference to my answer of 1 June 2015 to Question 157 consideration is being given to how best to contact the small proportion of affected individuals remaining. I am happy to meet the hon. Member to discuss this issue.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348133/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-09T15:29:13.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348133/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348133/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-02","Armed Forces: Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 1 June 2015 to Question 157, on the right of armed forces personnel to make a complaint following their illegal punishment following the receipt of a police caution in the last year and with reference to the contribution of the hon. Member for Broxtowe on 2 February 2015, Official Report, column 64, in which she gave a commitment to place notices in the usual places such as websites and magazines, if he will make a similar commitment; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","905"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348134","Department of Health","false","2015-06-10","<p>The Cancer Drugs Fund has already helped over 72,000 people in England and this year £340 million will be provided so people get the drugs they need.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The operation of the Cancer Drugs Fund (CDF), including which drugs remain in the Fund, is a matter for NHS England. The national CDF list is reviewed regularly and includes several treatments for pancreatic cancers such as:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Albumin Bound Paclitaxel (Abraxane) for the first line treatment of advanced adenocarcinoma of the pancreas in combination with gemcitabine; Peptide Receptor Radionucleotide Therapy for the treatment of advanced pancreatic neuroendocrine tumours; and Sunitinib (Sutent) for the treatment of pancreatic neuroendocrine carcinomas.</p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348134/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-10T16:23:13.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348134/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348134/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-02","Pancreatic Cancer: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will take steps to ensure that the treatments for pancreatic cancer listed by the Cancer Drugs Fund will continue to be made available to patients on the NHS.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","917"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348135","Home Office","false","2015-06-08","<p>To increase awareness of the risks of new psychoactive substances (NPS), the Government recently introduced the Psychoactive Substances Bill, which will bring in a blanket ban of NPS by prohibiting and disrupting production, distribution, sale and supply in the UK. The Bill will give police and other law enforcement agencies greater powers to tackle the trade in NPS, targeting suppliers who profit from their sale with complete disregard for the potential risks and consequences. As the Bill passes through parliament there will be various communication and media opportunities to raise awareness of the dangers of NPS.</p><p>There is a wide-ranging cross-Government programme of work in place to tackle new psychoactive substances (NPS), including activity to raise awareness and tackle use amongst young people. For example, we have:</p><p>• in March 2015, published a resource pack, written in partnership with front line practitioners, to enable those working with young people to have conversations with NPS users and challenge their drug use by raising awareness of the risks and consequences.</p><p>• delivered a new online resilience building resource, ‘Rise Above’, aimed at 11 to 16-year-olds, which provides resources to help develop skills to make positive choices for their health, including avoiding drug use.</p><p>• continued to update FRANK, the Government’s drugs information and advice service, to reflect new and emerging patterns of drug use and evolve to remain in line with young people’s media habits.</p><p>• the Home Office Forensic Early Warning System (FEWS) was set up in January 2011 to bolster national capacity to identify new psychoactive substances (NPS) available in the UK. It brings together expertise from forensic laboratories and chemical standard suppliers, UK-wide law enforcement agencies and experts in the field. FEWS continues to enable us to effectively assess the availability of NPS and take appropriate action.</p><p>• every year since 2009, Ministers have written to approximately 50 music festival organisers highlighting NPS dangers and calling on them to adopt a ‘no-legal highs’ policy for their festivals.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348135/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T10:47:58.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348135/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348135/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-06-02","Drugs: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she is taking to raise awareness of the dangers of legal highs amongst young people.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348136","Home Office","false","2015-06-08","<p>The Government introduced the Psychoactive Substances Bill in the House of Lords on 28 May. The Bill will make it a criminal offence to produce, supply, offer to supply, possess with intent to supply, import and export psychoactive substances. The blanket ban will give police and other law enforcement agencies greater powers to tackle the reckless trade in psychoactive substances.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348136/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T10:47:00.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348136/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348136/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-06-02","Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when she expects to being forward legislation to ban the sale of so-called legal highs; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","932"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348137","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-08","<p>My Department does not monitor the purchases of property by foreign buyers.</p><p> </p><p>The housing market is at the heart of our long-term economic plan – getting homes built, creating new homeowners and delivering hundreds of thousands of jobs. Foreign investment is helping to deliver new housing for UK residents and supporting jobs and long-term economic growth.</p><p> </p><p>Following the financial crisis and subsequent recession, foreign investment in new housing has been helping to provide the finance needed to build homes. Without upfront investment from buyers, financiers would not have released the cash needed for development to go ahead, and building would have stalled.</p><p> </p><p>These new developments not only provide homes, they also unlock associated affordable housing development In 2013, Savills suggested in their report “Spotlight World in London” that international sales of newly built properties helped to finance 3,000 new affordable homes that may otherwise not have been built.</p><p> </p><p>In their report of July 2014, Savills estimate that “those buying an investment property from overseas only account for an estimated 7 per cent of all greater London residential transactions”.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348137/answer",,,,,"799","2015-06-08T13:25:08.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348137/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348137/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-02","Housing: Foreign Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate he has made of the value of UK property sold to foreign buyers between 2010 and 2015.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","933"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348138","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-08","<p>The Department has received some proposed changes to the National Rail Conditions of Carriage from the Association of Train Operating Companies which we are now considering.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348138/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T11:00:18.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348138/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348138/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-02","Railways: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether he has recently received a revised draft of the National Rail Conditions of Carriage from the Association of Train Operating Companies for his approval.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","885"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348139","Department for Education","false","2015-06-08","<p>Academy Orders for Prendergast, Prendergast Vale and Prendergast Ladywell Schools were approved at the South East and South London Headteacher Board meeting on 26 February 2015. The Headteacher Board advises the Regional Schools Commissioner on the strength of all schools that apply to become academies.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>It is for schools to ensure that they have complied with relevant requirements at the point that they make their application. We will amend the application form and update associated guidance to highlight the requirements of regulation 46 of the School Governance (Federations) (England) Regulations 2012 (SI 2012/1035) for federated schools wishing to become academies.</p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348139/answer",,,,,"814","2015-06-08T15:37:32.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348139/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348139/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-06-02","Academies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will amend her Department's Governors' handbook and the Academy Converter Checklist for Schools to better highlight the requirements of regulation 46 of the School Governance (Federations)(England) Regulations 2012 (SI 2012/1035).","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","815"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348140","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-08","<p /> <p>We will set out our policy design in due course. As we develop the detailed policy we will ensure that those in need of support for their housing needs continue to receive it while ensuring the overall system is fair to the taxpayer, maintains work incentives and is not more generous to unemployed young people than to those working or studying to improve their prospects.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348140/answer",,,,,"888","2015-06-08T14:34:14.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348140/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348140/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-02","Housing Benefit: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many 18-21 year olds who (a) are care leavers, (b) have young children and (c) are in employment he has estimated would no longer receive housing benefit under the Government's proposals to restrict access for that age group.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","886"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348141","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-08","<p>The detailed policy design of the Youth Allowance is still being developed. The information is therefore not yet available.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348141/answer",,,,,"889","2015-06-08T09:48:12.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348141/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348141/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-02","Unemployment Benefits: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many 18-21 year olds he has estimated would be affected by plans to replace out-of-work benefits for that age group with a youth allowance.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","887"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348142","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-08","<p>We will set out our policy design in due course. As we develop the detailed policy we will ensure that those in need of support for their housing needs continue to receive it while ensuring the overall system is fair to the taxpayer, maintains work incentives and is not more generous to unemployed young people than to those working or studying to improve their prospects.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348142/answer",,,,,"886","2015-06-08T14:34:14.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348142/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348142/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-02","Housing Benefit: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many young people he has estimated will no longer receive housing benefit under the Government's proposals to restrict access for that age group to that benefit.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","888"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348143","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-08","<p>The detailed policy design of the Youth Allowance is still being developed. The information is therefore not yet available.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348143/answer",,,,,"887","2015-06-08T09:48:13.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348143/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348143/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-02","Employment and Support Allowance: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many young people under the Government's proposals for a youth allowance he has estimated will be expected to undertake community work from the commencement of an employment and support allowance claim.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","889"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348144","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-08","<p>We remain concerned about the case of Asia Bibi and the court’s decision to uphold the imposition of the death penalty for blasphemy. We hope the verdict will be overturned at the next appeal. On 28 October 2014, I raised our concerns on Ms Bibi’s case with the Pakistan High Commissioner. On 5 December 2014 the Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron) stressed our concerns about Pakistan’s blasphemy law with Prime Minister Sharif. The Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond), discussed Pakistan’s misuse of the blasphemy laws with Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif in November 2014.</p><p>We continue to urge the Government of Pakistan to protect the human rights of all its citizens as laid down in the Constitution and in accordance with international standards.</p><p>Our concerns about religious freedom in Pakistan are documented in the Foreign and Commonwealth Office’s annual Human Rights report and quarterly updates.</p><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348144/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T12:27:10.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348144/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348144/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-02","Pakistan: Religious Freedom","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with the government of Pakistan on the issue of religious freedom (a) in relation to the case of Asia Bibi and (b) in general.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","835"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348145","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-04","<p>I have had no recent discussions with either Ministerial colleagues or representatives from the steel industry with regard to Tata Steel’s plans to close the British Steel pension scheme.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348145/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-04T15:06:52.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348145/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348145/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-02","British Steel: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent discussions he has had with (a) ministerial colleagues and (b) representatives from the steel industry on Tata Steel's plans to close the British Steel pension scheme.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","843"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348146","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-09","<p>The Government has said that it will give Parliament the opportunity to repeal the Hunting Act on a free vote, with a government bill in government time.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348146/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-09T10:22:44.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348146/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348146/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-02","Hunting Act 2004","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what her policy is on repeal of the Hunting Act.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","906"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348147","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-10","<p /> <p>The information requested, for those subject to the removal of the spare room subsidy, is not readily available at constituency level (Camden, Peckham, and Southwark); and could only be obtained at a disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348147/answer",,,,,"909","2015-06-10T16:40:30.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348147/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348147/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-02","Housing Benefit: Social Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of how many (a) single-parent households, (b) households with dependent children, (c) households with a disabled member, (d) pensioner households and (e) households with one or more person employed in Camberwell and Peckham constituency are subject to the under-occupancy penalty.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","907"
