"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348175","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-08","<p /> <p>The Department for Work and Pensions (DWP) will publish figures on the number of hardship applications and awards in the summer of 2015.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348175/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T09:53:04.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348175/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348175/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-02","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to the Answer of 24 March 2015 to Question 228133, how much has been claimed in hardship payments in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","748"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348176","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-10","<p /> <p>The information requested is not available.</p><p> </p><p>Our forecasts of Housing Benefit caseload and expenditure do not take an explicit view of the number of people who will be subject to the removal of spare room subsidy.</p><p> </p><p>Forecasts are based on the assumption that future expenditure will be in line with what would happen if the proportion of social tenants who have a reduction remains constant, but do not take a view as to whether the associated savings will manifest as actual under-occupancy reductions, or through behavioural change (e.g. moving into work, or into a smaller property).</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348176/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-10T16:43:43.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348176/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348176/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-02","Housing Benefit: Social Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the number of people who will be affected by the under-occupancy penalty between 2015 and 2020.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","722"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348177","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-08","<p /> <p>The Government’s commitment to save £12bn from welfare spending was set out in its election manifesto. Further details will be given in due course.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348177/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T15:35:11.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348177/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348177/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-02","Social Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when he will announce details of how his Department will reduce spending on social security by £12 billion by 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","723"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348178","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-05","<p /> <p>Historic and forecast Housing Benefit caseload and expenditure are available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/416959/Outturn-and-forecast-Budget-2015.xlsx" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/416959/Outturn-and-forecast-Budget-2015.xlsx</a></p><p> </p><p>The effect of rising numbers of working claimants can be seen in the lines showing the ‘Housing Benefit / Council Tax Benefit only’ group, nearly all of whom are in work, and who are receiving Housing Benefit only on the grounds of being low income renters.</p><p> </p><p>Further detailed statistics on Housing Benefit caseload and average weekly amounts are available at <a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk</a>.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348178/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-05T10:59:20.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348178/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348178/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-02","Housing Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effect of changes in the number of working people claiming housing benefit on housing benefit spending.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","724"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348179","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-08","<p /> <p>We will publish a full Impact Assessment in due course.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348179/answer",,,,,"742 ; 743 ; 744","2015-06-08T14:45:23.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348179/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348179/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-02","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the effect on the number of families living in temporary accommodation of reducing the benefit cap from £26,000 to £23,000 per year.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","725"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348180","Department of Health","false","2015-06-09","<p>No such comparative research has been undertaken. Public Health England does not collect data on whether an individual is in a same sex relationship or a civil partnership as part of the routine surveillance of acute hepatitis B or HIV, nor as part of routine surveillance in blood donors.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348180/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-09T11:39:31.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348180/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348180/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-02","Viral Diseases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what comparative research his Department has made on the incidence of Hepatitis B and HIV infection in the population of (a) men who have sex with men (MSM) and (b) the MSM population in civil partnerships or same sex marriages; what assessment his Department has made on this incidence in respect of the safety of blood donation; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Michael Fabricant","Lichfield","Michael Fabricant","740"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348181","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-08","<p>The UK has a comprehensive anti-money laundering (AML) and counter financing of terrorism regime‎ and we are committed to ensuring our financial system is a hostile environment for illicit finances.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Treasury is responsible for appointing AML supervisors, including the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA). The FCA is responsible for ensuring compliance of financial institutions (including HSBC, Barclays, and Standard Chartered) with their AML requirements.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The FCA is operationally independent from Government and carries out its functions within the framework of statutory objectives and duties agreed by Parliament.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The FCA is discussing with banks whether the FIFA episode has highlighted weaknesses in their AML systems and controls.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348181/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T16:34:36.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348181/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348181/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-02","FIFA: Money Laundering","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent discussions he has had with representatives of (a) HSBC, (b) Barclays and (c) Standard Chartered about allegations that their banks have been involved in money laundering by senior officials in world football administration.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","759"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348182","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-10","<p>The Overseas Territories are separate jurisdictions with their own democratically elected Governments, Constitutions and laws under which Territory authorities are responsible for the regulation of banks. It is primarily for the law enforcement authorities of the Territories to deal with any allegations brought to them. UK law enforcement authorities would only become involved if the allegations involved criminality in the United Kingdom.</p><p>The Caribbean Overseas Territories and Bermuda are active members of the Caribbean Financial Action Task Force, one of Financial Action Task Force associated bodies. They are subject to evaluations of their anti-money laundering regimes through this body and these assessments are publicly available.</p><p>The UK and Territory Governments have a shared agenda on the application of high international standards for financial regulation. Most recently at the 2014 Joint Ministerial Council Territory Leaders agreed to work with the UK in raising international standards to tackle money laundering, tax evasion, illicit finance and corruption.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348182/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-10T16:02:44.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348182/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348182/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-02","British Overseas Territories: Money Laundering","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what power the Government has to investigate private banks registered in British Overseas Territories for alleged money laundering.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","762"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348183","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-08","<p>The information requested is not held centrally and can only be collated at disproportionate costs.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348183/answer",,,,,,"2015-06-08T13:21:33.62Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348183/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348183/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-02","Tony Blair","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will publish details of each (a) meeting and (b) overnight stay by Tony Blair in each UK embassy in each year between 2010 and 2014.","false","Biography information for Andrew Bridgen","North West Leicestershire","Andrew Bridgen","770"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348184","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-06-10","<p /> <p>Whilst crime is falling, since 2010 offenders are more likely to go to prison, and for longer. Sentencing in individual cases is a matter for our independent courts taking into account all the circumstances of each case. In order to pass a custodial sentence the court must be satisfied that the offence is so serious that neither a fine alone nor a community order can be justified.</p><p> </p><p>The number of people sentenced to immediate custody by gender, offence type and length of sentence, from 2010 to 2014, (the latest information available) in the North Wales police force area, can be viewed in table 1 and table 1A.</p><p> </p><p>The proportion of women sentenced to immediate custody within Wales police force area, from 2010 to 2014 (the latest information available), can be viewed in the table 2.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348184/answer","Hanson 787-788.xls","Hanson 787-788.xls","Tables highlighting sentencing information","Tables highlighting sentencing information","788","2015-06-10T10:10:54.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348184/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348184/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-06-02","Custodial Treatment: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people and of what gender in each North Wales police force area committed an offence resulting in immediate custody in each year since 2011; and what the offence type and length of sentence was in each such year.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","787"
